212c77a category-preview\">0<!-- --> <!-- -->answers</span></div><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-count\">0</span></button></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a sidebar-card support-card\"><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a support-label\">Still stuck?</p><h3 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Chat with our team</h3><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Share your situation and we&#x27;ll recommend the best park, indoor option, or community meetup.</p><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a support-actions\"><a href=\"/contact\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Contact us</a><a href=\"/signup\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a secondary\">Join community</a></div></div></aside><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-main\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-rail\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-eyebrow\">Popular right now</span><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Tap to jump to the full answer.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip-row\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>Is there a free dog park in Danville, VA?</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>Can I walk my dog on the Danville Riverwalk?</button></div></div><div role=\"list\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-accordion\"><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">01</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Is there a free dog park in Danville, VA?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">The city-operated Coates Bark Park requires a $20 annual membership.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Facilities &amp; Features</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">The city-operated Coates Bark Park requires a $20 annual membership. However, the nearby Pittsylvania County Dog Park in Chatham is available for free public use.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Facilities &amp; Features</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">02</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Can I walk my dog on the Danville Riverwalk?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Yes, the Riverwalk Trail is strictly dog-friendly for leashed pets, offering miles of paved paths along the Dan River that connect major parks and the River District.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Planning Your Visit</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Yes, the Riverwalk Trail is strictly dog-friendly for leashed pets, offering miles of paved paths along the Dan River that connect major parks and the River District.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Planning Your Visit</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article></div></div></div></div></section></div></section><section id=\"related-resources\" class=\"related-resources-section\"><div class=\"section-shell\"><div class=\"section-heading\"><span class=\"section-eyebrow\">Keep exploring</span><h2>More ways to plan</h2><p>Browse statewide guides, submit a listing, or connect with our team.</p></div><div class=\"resources-grid\"><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-globe\"></i></div><h3>California overview</h3><p>See every city we cover plus statewide insights.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/contact\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-chat-dots\"></i></div><h3>Ask the team</h3><p>Need custom data or media assets? We’re here.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/list-your-park\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-megaphone\"></i></div><h3>Feature your park</h3><p>Upgrade to a featured listing and reach active pet parents.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/blog\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-journal-text\"></i></div><h3>Latest guides</h3><p>Training tips, travel itineraries, and product spotlights.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a></div></div></section></main><footer class=\"footer-new\"><